editorialSummary.text: Laid-back joint serving an eclectic menu of Asian-inspired plates, plus craft cocktails, beer, and wine.

originalText.text:

originalText.text: I want to give five stars to the kind waiter. The experience was beautiful, and the food was super tasty and excellent. I recommend this place and suggest that you try it too. The staff working here are very kind and unique as well. All the dishes were delicious, but my favourite was the honey butter chicken wings. However, every dish was interesting to taste and enjoy.

originalText.text: This place is a lovely combination of sophisticated and laidback atmospheres. The staff is friendly and attentive.  We ordered crisp cocktails to complement the flavors of the food. Their fried rice was perfect, the cucumbers were nicely flavored, the highlight was the complimentary fresh baked roll with sambal sauce butter.

originalText.text: Went here back in 2022 and was staying at the hotel across the street. My wife and I wanted some place to eat so at first, we went to another bar down the street and when I saw their menu (it looked like pictures off a pool menu from the 90s-00s), we decided to leave and give this place a try due to proximity. What a fantastic turn of events when we walked into this place. Unsure of what to expect we walked and got a seat. We were told it was Restaurant Week and they had a special menu, when I tell you right now it was the best meal I‚Äôve ever had, probably in my life. Everything and I mean everything on that 5-course meal was delicious (my wife got a different option than I did so we could try basically everything on the menu) and the service was fantastic. I just thought about that meal, specifically the 5-spice cake with green apple sorbet for dessert and just how it blew my mind the combination. Whenever I go back to Manhattan I will be coming back to try something else! Loved the bathroom by the way
